- Technical leader (Cisco Metapod - OpenStack), Cisco Systems,
  Greater Los Angeles Area, CA
  January 2014 - June 2018

  Member of the leadership team responsible for Cisco Metapod.

  > Cisco Metapod.  An on premise production-ready, OpenStack-based cloud, we
    engineer, deploy, and operate on the customer's behalf. This includes a
    converged single OpenStack story among our recent acquisitions and existing
    business units.

  Led a distributed team of motivated engineers, whom were responsible for mid
  to long-term improvements of the products. Included development of a
  deployment/inventory framework for Cisco Metapod, which was used by CI,
  developers, and operations throughout Cisco. Tooling to aid in the
  aforementioned (Molecule[1], Gilt[2], Photon[3]).  Product releases, which
  included major, minor, and skipped versions of OpenStack and Ceph upgrades.
  Worked closely with Ops to identify and correct pain points in the platform.
  Inventory API, validator, and generator which was consumed by Ansible and other
  services.  Password rotation tooling for OpenStack and ancillary services.

  The products are composed of many layers, for which I was intimately involved.
  Responsibilities included working with product on the roadmap, leading beyond
  my team to converge projects and codebases, code and architecture reviews,
  HA strategies, on-call, bug fixes, and feature adds.

